{ A typical situation from the Four Pawns Attack. White has an impressive center, but Black has a lot of active pieces and pressure against the center. Can you spot the best way to proceed ? }
1... Nxe5
{ This wins a pawn.  Retreating with   11...Be7  =+  is probably still better for Black, but the mainline is superior. }
2. dxe5
{ 12.Ned2  is the most tenacious, but Black is simply up a pawn.  Nxf3+  13.Nxf3  Bf6  -+ }
2... Qxd1+ 3. Rxd1 Bxf3 4. gxh4 Bxh1 *

