{ In this chapter we engage with positions that result after a pawn exchange on e5. With the space advantage on the kingside and the misplaced black knight, White has chances to start a dangerous attack on a short castled king. On the other hand, Black might get play in the center and on the queenside  (beware of the square c2)  , and the e5-pawn can become a weakness. }
