{ Can you find the correct path in this confusing situation ? } 1. Rxf5
{ The start of an amazing ambush. } 1... exf5 2. Nf6+ gxf6 3. Qxf5 fxg5
{ 18...hxg5  makes things a little easier for White.  19.Bd3 !  Rfe8  20.Qh7+  Kf8  21.exf6  +-  and mate. }
4. Bd3 Rfe8
{ 19...Rfd8  is subtly different.  20.Qh7+  Kf8  21.Qxh6+ !   21.Be4 ?  doesn't work here.  Bd2 !!  22.Bf2   22.Qxh6+  Ke8  23.Qh8+  Ke7 =  22...Qe6  23.Bf5  Qe8  without the bishop on d2 Qxh6 would be easily winning now, but with g5 protected White has to settle for a perpetual.  24.Qh8+  Ke7  25.Qf6+ =  21...Ke8  22.Qh8+  Kd7  23.Bf5+  +- }
5. Qh7+ Kf8 6. Be4
{ Chess is a weird game and here things are completely opposite to 19... Rfd8. Be4 wins and   21.Qxh6+  doesn't.  After  Ke7  22.Qf6+  White again only has a perpetual since   22.Bxg5+  Kd7  23.Bf5+  Re6  -+  is even winning for Black. }
6... Qe6
{ Here   21...Bd2  doesn't work because after  22.Qxh6+  the rook blocks e8 and Black's king has to run into  Ke7  23.Bxg5+  Bxg5  24.Qxg5+  Kd7  25.Bxd5  +- }
7. Bf5 Qd5 8. Qxh6+ Ke7 9. Bxg5+ { Black's king is finally caught. } *

