{ Avoiding Nd6+, followed by Nxf5. Now, after Nd6, White isn't able to block the g-file anymore.   22...Bg4+ ?  23.Kg3  Be2+  24.Bg5 !  =+  If White can block the g-file, his chances of survival increase.   22...Kb8  23.Bf4+  e5  24.Nxe5  Qc2  25.Rae1  fxe5  26.Rxe5  Ka7  27.Bg3  Be4+  28.Rxe4  Qd3+  29.Re3  Nxe3  30.Qxe3  Qxf1  -+  should be winning for Black, too, though it's less clear-cut as the mainline. }
4. Bg5
{ 23.Nd6  Bg4+  24.Kg3  Bd1+  25.Kh4  Qc2  26.h3  Qe2  27.Qxh7+  Ne7  -+ } 4...
Qc2 { 23...Qxb2  -+  is good, too, but   23...Qc4  24.Qh4  ∓  is less clear. }
5. Kg3 Ke7
{ The g-file opens with devastating consequences for the white king. } *

